## Building a Memory (Flip-card) Game in React

**Mental model:** Cards are a shuffled array of paired symbols. Track which indices are *flipped* (currently face-up, max two) and which are *matched* (permanently up). On the second flip, compare: match keeps them; mismatch flips both back after a short delay. Lock input during that delay so a third card can't be flipped.

### Step 1 — Build a shuffled, paired deck
```jsx
const deck = useMemo(() => shuffle([...symbols, ...symbols].map((s, i) => ({ id: i, s }))), []);
```

### Step 2 — Flipped + matched state
```jsx
const [flipped, setFlipped] = useState([]); // indices, length 0..2
const [matched, setMatched] = useState(new Set());
```

### Step 3 — Flip logic with a lock
Ignore clicks on locked board, already-flipped, or matched cards.

```jsx
const flip = (i) => {
  if (lock || flipped.includes(i) || matched.has(i.id)) return;
  const next = [...flipped, i];
  setFlipped(next);
  if (next.length === 2) resolve(next);
};
```

### Step 4 — Resolve the pair
```jsx
const [a, b] = next;
if (deck[a].s === deck[b].s) { setMatched((m) => new Set([...m, a, b])); setFlipped([]); }
else { setLock(true); setTimeout(() => { setFlipped([]); setLock(false); }, 800); }
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Triple click | `lock` flag blocks a third flip during the delay. |
| Re-click flipped card | `flipped.includes` guard. |
| Win | All cards matched. |

**Interview tip:** The input `lock` during the mismatch delay is the bug-prone bit — without it a fast player flips a third card mid-animation and corrupts the pair state.

