## Building a Memory (Flip-card) Game in Vue 3

**Mental model:** A shuffled deck of paired symbols. Track `flipped` indices (max two) and a `matched` Set. The second flip compares: match → keep; mismatch → flip both back after a delay, with input *locked* during that window so a third card can't sneak in.

### Step 1 — Shuffled, paired deck
```js
const deck = ref(shuffle([...SYMBOLS, ...SYMBOLS]).map((s, i) => ({ id: i, s })));
```

### Step 2 — Flipped + matched state
```js
const flipped = ref([]);
const matched = ref(new Set());
const lock = ref(false);
```

### Step 3 — Flip with a lock guard
```js
function flip(i) {
  if (lock.value || flipped.value.includes(i) || matched.value.has(i)) return;
  flipped.value = [...flipped.value, i];
  if (flipped.value.length === 2) resolve();
}
```

### Step 4 — Resolve the pair
```js
const [a, b] = flipped.value;
if (deck.value[a].s === deck.value[b].s) { matched.value = new Set([...matched.value, a, b]); flipped.value = []; }
else { lock.value = true; setTimeout(() => { flipped.value = []; lock.value = false; }, 800); }
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Triple click | `lock` blocks the third flip. |
| Re-click flipped | `includes` guard. |
| Win | `matched.size === deck.length`. |

**Interview tip:** The input `lock` during the mismatch delay is the detail that prevents corruption — call it out, since a fast third click is exactly the bug interviewers probe.

